Sentencas: In order to develop high performance intermediate temperature (< 800 degrees C) solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with a lower fabrication cost, a pressurized spray process of ceramic suspensions has been established to prepare both dense yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolyte membranes and transition anode layers on NiO + YSZ anode supports.
Titulo: Thin yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte and transition layers fabricated by particle suspension spray

Sentencas: A single cell with 10 mu m thick YSZ electrolyte on a porous anode support and similar to 20 mu m thick cathode layer showed peak power densities of only 212 mW cm(-2) at 700 degrees C and 407 mW cm(-2) for 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Thin yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte and transition layers fabricated by particle suspension spray

Sentencas: While a cell with 10 mu m thick YSZ electrolyte and a transition layer on the porous anode support using a ultra-fine NiO + YSZ powder showed peak power densities of 346 and 837 mW cm(-2) at 700 and 800 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Thin yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte and transition layers fabricated by particle suspension spray

Sentencas: The dramatic improvement of cell performance was attributed to the much improved anode microstructure that was confirmed by both scanning electron microscopes (SEM) observation and impedance spectroscopy.
Titulo: Thin yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte and transition layers fabricated by particle suspension spray

Sentencas: The results have demonstrated that a pressurized spray coating is a suitable technique to fabricate high performance SOFCs and at lower cost.
Titulo: Thin yttria-stabilized zirconia electrolyte and transition layers fabricated by particle suspension spray
